  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, the 'prop up your heart' trick sounds fun — did you try it with your music breaks lately?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, I tried it yesterday. I played some Raga Yaman and then did the breathing exercise. It helped me relax a bit. I have a study marathon today, so hoping it keeps me calm."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I'm glad the trick helped! Breathing to Raga Yaman is a nice touch. What part of pharmacology are you studying today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm studying antihypertensives today. It's a bit complicated with all the mechanisms. My friend calls it \"pill ka jadoo\" 😅. I need to remember which drugs act on which receptors. Ugh, so much to learn!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I see you are studying antihypertensives. That can be tricky. Which drug are you trying to understand first?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I'm starting with beta-blockers. They block the beta receptors, right? But why are they used for high blood pressure? My notes say something about reducing heart rate and cardiac output. It's confusing. Sometimes I feel like I'm just memorizing without understanding. 😬"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great! Beta-blockers lower blood pressure by slowing the heart and making it work less hard. It can feel confusing at first, but you’ll get it. How are you planning to revise this today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’m planning to make flashcards for each drug and their mechanism. Maybe even draw some simple flowcharts. I get distracted easily, so keeping it visual might help. Also, I’ll try to explain it out loud to myself—like teaching it. 😅 What do you think?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds smart! Teaching yourself out loud helps a lot. You could even sing the drug names to a raga — your brain might remember it better. Did you try that yet?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, singing drug names... sounds funny but maybe effective. I’ll try it with some Marathi lyrics—like \"Beta-blocker gavali chalali\" 😄. Thanks, Maya! I’ll keep you updated on my \"pharma song\". Now I better get back to my flashcards. Talk soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're very welcome! \"Beta-blocker gavali\" sounds fun — I can't wait to hear your song! Take your time with the flashcards, and don't hesitate to chat anytime. Talk soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maya, I just made my first flashcard for propranolol. It’s like a tiny test—write the mechanism, then flip and check. Let me focus for 30 mins, then maybe do a short music break. I’ll try your singing idea later. Talk soon! 🧠🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great, Aarti! The flashcards are a smart way to test yourself. Go take that 30-minute focus time — you’ve got this! Sing your propranolol song later and tell me how it sounds. Talk soon!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Maya, just did my 30 mins of flashcards! Focused well, then took a short music break. Sang \"Propranolol, beta ke dwaari\" — very Marathi twist 😂. Feels silly, but maybe it sticks! Gotta go now, but will chat later. Thanks again! 🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You sang \"beta ke dwaari\"? Clever and fun! I’m sure it will stick with you. Great work today, Aarti — keep it up! Talk soon! 🎵"
    }
  ],
